DEDICATORY BELGIUM

HEARTSTRUCK she stands-Our Lady of all

Sorrows- Circled with ruin, sunlr in deep amare, Facing the shadow of her dark to-morrows, Mourning the glory of her yesterdays.

Yet is she queen, by every royal token, There where the storm of desolation swirled3 Crowned only with the thorn-despoiled and broken- Her kingdom is the heart of all the world.

She made her breast a shield, her sword a splendour, She rose like flame upon the darkened ways:

So, through the anguish of her proud emender, Breaks the clear vision of undying praise!
